<TITLE> Dhaka stocks falls for 3rd day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 13 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks continued to fall for the third consecutive day. Although selling pressure determined the general trend, the market rose sharply in the early hours with a 20 point rise. But the index continued its bumpy ride through the day to close lower than yesterday. A fund manger identified the recent trend as flat, and dominated by selling pressure. The benchmark general index (DGEN) shed 5.14 points or 0.09 percent to close at 5522.67. The day's turnover stood at Tk 7.26 billion, slightly lower than that of yesterday. Gainers led the day with 129 issues out of 240 issues advancing and 103 declining. Beximco led the turnover table with shares worth Tk 675.96 million changing hands, loosing slightly by 0.12 percent to close at Tk 397.50. DESCO followed with total turnover of Tk 422.36 million, gaining 2.57 percent to close at Tk 1779.75. Lone telecom issue Grmeenphone suffered mild losses of 1.84 percent to close at Tk 346.50 with shares worth Tk 395.76 million traded. Beximco Pharma gained marginally by 0.26 percent to close at Tk 188.60 and shares worth Tk 371.78 million being traded. Lanka Bangla Finance made nominal gains by 0.89 percent, closing at Tk 360.50 and trading Tk 302.71 million on the day. Price correction, low investors' confidence increased selling pressure in the market says chief executive of a fund management firm under condition of anonymity
